Species were then gathered into 20 groups based on their functional identity. The rank frequency diagrams (
      
       Figure 6
      ) reveal a strong dominance of two groups which are frequent and abundant, the presence of an intermediate group often present but not dominant, and a right-skewed tail containing many rare groups. Among the 20 groups, the two most abundant groups contribute, on average, to 34 and 24% respectively of the total local biomass while they only contain 3 and 8 species (out of 70), respectively (
      
       Figure 6
      ). These groups also occur very frequently (present in more than 75% of the 810 samples).
